  88:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****         (+) MspDeInitCallback  : SRAM MspDeInit.
  89:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       This function) takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
  90:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c **** 
  91:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       By default, after the HAL_SRAM_Init and if the state is HAL_SRAM_STATE_RESET
  92:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (overridden) functions.
  93:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
  94:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       reset to the legacy weak (overridden) functions in the HAL_SRAM_Init
  95:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       and  HAL_SRAM_DeInit only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
  96:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_SRAM_Init and HAL_SRAM_DeInit
  97:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
  98:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c **** 
  99:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 100:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 101:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 102:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       during the Init/DeInit.
 103:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 104:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       using HAL_SRAM_RegisterCallback before calling HAL_SRAM_DeInit
 105:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       or HAL_SRAM_Init function.
 106:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c **** 
 107:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       When The compilation define USE_HAL_SRAM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 108:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 109:Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_sram.c ****       and weak (overridden) callbacks are used.
